The most intense hurricane on record

The storm was headed west northwest, said National Hurricane Center director Bob Sheets.
At 3 p.m. today, the center of the storm was near latitude 22.3 north and longitude 92.9 west, or about 380 miles southeast of Brownsville, Texas, the National Weather Service said.
There were no reports of deaths.
Hundreds of homes were destroyed, he said.
In Campeche, boats were driven onto the street running along the waterfront, Ramon Castillo, a night watchman at the newspaper Novedades of Campeche, said in a telephone interview.
"There is no light, there is no radio, there is nothing.
There is much damage.
The whole city is flooded," he said.
